equation_narrative.headline: Hydrophobic core context drives valine prediction through structural contact reading
equation_narrative.story: The model assembles a strongly hydrophobic representation by reading 6 structural contacts within the ubiquitin core. Early layers (1-9) show volatile logit-lens outputs reflecting the accumulation of local hydrophobic features, with the representation character shifting between small hydrophobic residues (A, V) and polar residues (T, S) as different contact patterns are integrated. The perception phase (L1-23) builds a representation consistent with buried, hydrophobic positions through attention to nearby nonpolar residues. In the decision phase (L24-33), valine-specific prediction channels activate strongly at L27-32, with MLP neurons casting decisive votes for branched hydrophobic residues. The model correctly predicts valine with 55% confidence, narrowly outcompeting isoleucine (32%).

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a representation of position 26's biochemical context through structural contact reading. Six structural contacts are read, predominantly from nearby positions in the hydrophobic core. Early layers show high volatility in logit-lens outputs with 14 lead changes, reflecting the sequential integration of different information sources rather than prediction attempts. The representation character oscillates between small hydrophobics (A peaks at 29% at L21), polar residues (T reaches 47% at L11, S peaks at 20% at L13-23), and branched hydrophobics (V emerges at L5-9 with 53%). Attention heads at L9 show strong structural reading patterns (F9:5728, F9:1281 with 50+ projection), integrating local sequence context. By L23, the representation has stabilized around a hydrophobic character (V at 9%, L at 19%, A at 17%) consistent with a buried core position.
perception_phase.context_character: The assembled context by L23 indicates a buried hydrophobic position within ubiquitin's core, surrounded by nonpolar residues. The representation is consistent with small-to-medium hydrophobic residues, with weak polar signal suggesting some local sequence influence from adjacent charged residues (D24, E25, K27, K29).
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 6 residues within 8Å, predominantly hydrophobic core positions
L9 attention features: F9:5728 (54.4 proj), F9:1281 (50.1 proj) encode local hydrophobic context
L18 attention features: F18:5712 (25.4 proj), F18:6256 (24.2 proj) refine structural environment encoding
Single co-evolving position detected, indicating weak evolutionary constraint
L10-11 MLP activity: N10:4792 (0.55 proj for V), but strong polar erasure from N11:5003 (-0.82 proj) creates T spike at L11

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L24-27 when leucine-specific prediction channels activate strongly, with L peaking at 63% at L30. However, valine-specific neurons mount a sustained counteroffensive at L27-32. MLP layer 32 delivers the decisive shift with 8.85 total projection toward V, driven by highly specific neurons: N32:4434 (1.38 proj for V), N32:393 (1.23 proj for V), and N32:2325 (0.91 proj for V). Attention head L31:18 contributes a massive 2.87 projection through structural contact reading (79.5% attention to structural neighbors). The final competition between V (55%) and I (32%) reflects the model's uncertainty between branched aliphatic residues in this hydrophobic context.
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from context encoding to amino acid prediction. At L23, the logit lens shows distributed probability across hydrophobic residues (L 19%, A 17%, S 21%) reflecting representation character. At L24, leucine-specific prediction channels activate (L jumps to 30%), and MLP layer 24 shows strong negative total projection (-2.87), indicating active suppression of alternative candidates. This is when the representation transitions from 'encoding a hydrophobic buried position' to 'predicting specific branched aliphatics.'

candidates.narrative: Valine emerges as a serious contender at L27 (41%) after leucine's dominance at L24-30. The decisive push comes from MLP layers 31-32, where valine-specific neurons fire strongly: N31:3323 (0.94 proj), N31:4506 (0.92 proj), N31:4800 (0.83 proj), and the massive L32 contribution with N32:4434 (1.38 proj) leading the charge. Attention head L31:18 provides 2.87 projection through structural contact reading. V overtakes L permanently at L31, stabilizing at 55% by L33. The model's confidence in V over I (32%) suggests it has encoded the specific branching pattern and size constraints of this buried core position.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges L5-9 (53%), suppressed L10-23, resurges L27 (41%), dominant L31-33 (55%)
key_evidence: N32:4434 (1.38 proj) — V-specific with strong I secondary vote (1.24 proj)
N32:393 (1.23 proj) — V-specific with A secondary (0.73 proj)
L31:18 attention head (2.87 proj) — structural writer with 79.5% attention to contacts
N31:3323 (0.94 proj), N31:4506 (0.92 proj), N31:4800 (0.83 proj) — sustained V support

candidates.narrative: Isoleucine steadily accumulates support throughout the decision phase, rising from 2.5% at L23 to 31.6% at L33. It benefits from the same hydrophobic core context as valine, with many V-voting neurons also casting secondary votes for I (e.g., N32:4434 votes 1.38 for V, 1.24 for I). The model's difficulty distinguishing V from I reflects the chemical similarity of these branched aliphatics. I never leads but maintains consistent growth, suggesting the representation encodes 'branched hydrophobic' more strongly than the specific V vs I distinction.
key_evidence: N32:4434 secondary vote (1.24 proj for I) — nearly as strong as V vote
Consistent MLP support across L29-32 from neurons voting for branched hydrophobics
Final 32% probability indicates strong compatibility with assembled context

candidates.narrative: Leucine dominates the decision phase from L24-30, peaking at 63% at L30 before collapsing to 9% by L33. The L24 MLP activates leucine-specific channels (L jumps from 19% to 30%), and this support builds through L29 (56%). However, L30-32 MLP neurons actively suppress L: N30:3099 (-0.77 proj) erases leucine despite voting for other hydrophobics. The dramatic reversal suggests the model initially interprets the hydrophobic context as favoring the slightly larger leucine, but late-stage refinement based on precise structural constraints shifts to the smaller valine.
candidates.key_layers: Leads L24-30 (peaks 63% at L30), collapses L31-33 (9%)
key_evidence: L24 MLP activation drives L from 19% to 30%
N30:3099 (-0.77 proj) — erases L while voting for other residues
L31-32: catastrophic collapse as V-specific neurons overwhelm L support

candidates.narrative: Threonine peaks at 47% at L11, reflecting the logit-lens projection of a representation that has accumulated polar signal from adjacent charged residues (D24, E25, K27). This is NOT a prediction attempt — the model is still in perception mode, building a representation of local context. The T spike occurs when MLP layer 11 strongly erases hydrophobic signal (N11:5003 with -0.82 proj votes for polar residues). By L13, attention refocuses on structural contacts and T declines, eventually reaching 1.3% at L33 as the decision phase confirms the hydrophobic character.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks L11 (47%), declines L13-23, eliminated by L29 (2.7%)
key_evidence: L11 MLP: N11:5003 (-0.82 proj) erases V while voting for I, M, E
Logit lens artifact reflecting temporary polar representation character
Adjacent charged residues (D24, E25, K27, K29) provide local polar context

candidates.narrative: Alanine shows sustained logit-lens prominence through L3-23, peaking at 29% at L21. This reflects the representation's encoding of 'small hydrophobic' character as the model reads structural contacts from the buried core. The representation is consistent with small nonpolar residues during this phase, but this is not a prediction — it's the accumulation of size and hydrophobicity features. Once decision-phase neurons activate at L24+, A is rapidly suppressed (drops to 2% by L29) as the model commits to larger branched residues.
candidates.key_layers: Prominent L3-23 (peaks 29% at L21), eliminated L24-29
key_evidence: L20-21: A peaks as representation encodes small hydrophobic character
L24+ decision neurons suppress A in favor of branched residues
Final 1% indicates incompatibility with refined structural constraints

turning_points.description: A dramatic representation character shift occurs when L11 MLP neurons (N11:5003, -0.82 proj) strongly erase hydrophobic signal, causing threonine to spike to 47% in the logit lens. This reflects the integration of polar context from adjacent charged residues (D24, E25, K27, K29). L13 attention (3.53 total delta, 3.21 from attention) refocuses on structural contacts, and the representation shifts back toward hydrophobic character. This volatility is characteristic of perception-phase information integration, not prediction uncertainty.

The perception-to-decision transition occurs as amino acid-specific prediction channels activate. L24 MLP (total -2.87 proj) suppresses the distributed hydrophobic representation while activating leucine-specific features, causing L to jump from 19% to 30%. L27 marks the emergence of valine as a serious contender (41%) through attention head L27:16 (1.75 proj). This is when the model shifts from 'this is a buried hydrophobic position' to 'this should be leucine or valine specifically.'

The final decision crystallizes through massive MLP neuron activity. L30 sees leucine peak at 63%, but L31 MLP (3.49 total proj) activates strongly V-specific neurons: N31:3323 (0.94), N31:4506 (0.92), N31:4800 (0.83). L32 delivers the decisive blow with 8.85 total MLP projection, led by N32:4434 (1.38 proj for V). Simultaneously, attention head L31:18 contributes 2.87 proj through structural contact reading (79.5% attention to structural neighbors). V overtakes L at L31 and stabilizes at 55%.

deep_dives.label: Structural contact reading L9
deep_dives.caption: Layer 9 attention features encode the local hydrophobic context through structural contact reading. F9:5728 (54.4 proj) and F9:1281 (50.1 proj) show how the model integrates information from nearby core residues. These features represent 'this position is surrounded by hydrophobic residues' rather than predicting a specific amino acid.

deep_dives.label: Representation character shifts L10-23
deep_dives.caption: Track how the logit-lens outputs oscillate as different information sources are integrated. The T spike at L11, S prominence at L13-23, and A peak at L20-21 reflect the representation's evolving character, not prediction attempts. Notice how attention-driven events (L13, L18, L19, L23) refine the representation toward hydrophobic character.

deep_dives.label: Perception to decision L23-25
deep_dives.caption: L24 MLP shows -2.87 total projection, actively suppressing the distributed representation while activating L-specific channels. N24:1826 (-0.60 proj) erases charged residues, N24:1953 (-0.29 proj) erases polar residues. This is where amino acid-specific prediction neurons first dominate over context-encoding features.

deep_dives.label: Leucine dominance L27-30
deep_dives.caption: Watch leucine rise to 63% at L30 through sustained MLP support, then examine why it collapses. N30:3099 (-0.77 proj) actively erases L despite the hydrophobic context. This suggests the model refines from 'large hydrophobic' to 'medium branched hydrophobic' based on precise structural constraints.

deep_dives.label: Valine-specific neurons L31-32
deep_dives.caption: The decisive layers where V overtakes L. L31 shows 3.49 total projection with three strong V-specific neurons (N31:3323, N31:4506, N31:4800). L32 delivers 8.85 total projection, the largest MLP contribution in the entire forward pass, led by N32:4434 (1.38 proj for V, 1.24 for I). These neurons encode 'branched medium hydrophobic in buried core' with high specificity.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L31-32
deep_dives.caption: L31:18 provides 2.87 projection through structural contact reading (79.5% attention to structural neighbors), the single largest attention contribution. L32:16 adds 1.77 proj with 30.5% structural attention. These heads read the precise 3D environment to confirm valine's compatibility with the assembled structural context.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts valine by assembling a representation of position 26 as a buried hydrophobic core position through structural contact reading in layers 1-23, then activating valine-specific prediction neurons in layers 31-32. The strongest evidence comes from MLP layer 32 (8.85 total projection) and attention head L31:18 (2.87 projection from structural contacts). The close competition with isoleucine (32%) and the temporary leucine dominance (63% at L30) reflect the model's encoding of 'branched aliphatic in hydrophobic core' with some uncertainty about the precise size and branching pattern. The decision crystallizes when late-stage neurons (N32:4434, N32:393, N32:2325) cast highly specific votes for valine based on the refined structural constraints.
